/* FreeJoy Configurator — light theme overrides.
 *
 * INTENTIONALLY EMPTY. All theme colour now comes from the QPalette set in
 * MainWindow::themeChanged(); every QSS rule lives in common.qss and is either
 * palette()-driven or uses a theme-independent accent/icon. This is what lets
 * the stylesheet be applied ONCE and a theme swap be a cheap palette change
 * instead of a multi-second full-tree QSS repolish.
 *
 * DO NOT add theme-specific rules here: themeChanged applies the sheet only
 * once, so anything added here would not take effect on a later toggle. If you
 * genuinely need a colour the palette can't express, drive it from the palette
 * or a theme-independent token in common.qss, or draw it in code at paint time.
 *
 * (The old light-theme group-box border override is gone: the light palette's
 * Mid role is already #cccccc, which common.qss's `border: 1px solid
 * palette(mid)` picks up.)
 */
